      • getResult

        public java.lang.Object getResult()
        Get response of sync.
        Returns:
        HashMap instance.

        Example :
        
 HashMap<String, HashMap<String, Object>> mainHashMap = (HashMap<String, HashMap<String, Object>>) syncResult.getResult();
 HashMap<String, Object> innerMap = (HashMap<String, Object>) mainHashMap.get(class_uid);
        

 //For created, updated and deleted list
 //If error is present then it returns null
        
 ArrayList<BuiltObject> createdAtList = (ArrayList<BuiltObject>) innerMap.get(BuiltConstant.KEY_CREATED);
        

 //For error detail
 BuiltError error = innerMap.get(BuiltConstant.KEY_ERROR);

 Outer HashMap key - class uid
 Inner HashMap Key - BuiltConstant.KEY_CREATED, BuiltConstant.KEY_UPDATED, BuiltConstant.KEY_DELETED, and BuiltConstant.KEY_ERROR
